      "long-abstract": "<!--[CDATA[p {margin-bottom: 0.1in;line-height: 120.0%;}a:link {}]]-->Each year, the number of Internet of Things (IoT) devices is growing exponentially, fueling digital transformation of industries and enterprises. However, IoT and its applications are often misunderstood and not considered with an end-to-end integration mindset. The challenges of IoT systems can be simplied with tools, processes, and methods already existing in DevOps. In this session, partners Accenture and Red Hat will explain how a solid platform and three-tier architecture using open source technology are key to building and benefiting from IoT systems. You2019ll gain an understanding of how IoT systems and DevOps are made compatible by adapting DevOps tools and processes and using a simple architecture to develop IoT applications, with examples of how partners are supporting digital transformation."
